fields.name: The Stairway to Heaven Trail Race 2019
fields.friendlyname: The Stairway to Heaven Trail Race 2019

fields.name: Holme Valley 5 Miler
fields.keyinfo: An out and back 5 mile race along Brown Hill Lane / Kiln Bent Road / Holme Woods Lane. 211m of gradual climb on the way out, but it's all down hill on the way back ... and there's BBQ and bar open after.
fields.description:
Which club will win our fabulous 1st male and female Team Trophy in our inaugural year? Not in a club? You can still run as an individual.

Earn your special bonus medal to enhance the South Huddersfield Trail and Road Series 2019 medal collection.

Teams are calculated as you cross the line.

fields.name: Holme Valley Trail Half Marathon
fields.keyinfo: The only event of it's kind in the stunning Holme Valley.
fields.description:
The course is based on a two lap version of the sell out Stairway To Heaven trail race.

Race includes:

13.1 miles of challenging trails and country lanes. 
Stunning panoramic views
Water station on route.
Bespoke Medal which interlocks with the South Huddersfield Trail and Road Series collection. 
Cake by Holmbridge Church
Food available and bar open
Volunteer first aid and safety support
Race licensed and insured by the Association of Running Clubs
Wild and wet weather - or just maybe the most beautiful weather ever?
Mud, steep rocky ascents and descents
Awards to:

Men’s and Women's 1st, 2nd & 3rd, 1st V40, 1st V45, 1st V50, 1st V55, 1st V60, 1st V65, 1st V70
Team: 1st mens and 1st womens team of 3

fields.name: The School Run
fields.keyinfo: 9km of 100% trail around the stunning Digley Reservoir area
fields.description:
The School Run is a scenic and challenging course entirely off road. Run down from Holme School to Digley reservoir on little know paths before running a figure of 8 shaped course on hilly and varied trails. Climb back to finish. Approx 9km.

Summer Wine Trails events include the main trail race as well as a Challenge Walk version which sets off 1 hour earlier as well as children's races. All our events are be licensed and insured through the Association of Running Clubs.

It's not flat.

fields.name: The Windmill 6
fields.keyinfo: An undulating 6 Miles of road around the Windmills of Spicer Hill.
fields.description: Birdsedge First School presents a undulating road race around the Windmills on the top of Spicer Hill. The route is an anti-clockwise loop around the windmills and taking in the breathtaking views across Huddersfield Wakefield, Penistone and surrounding areas.

fields.name: Toss O Coin
fields.keyinfo: Toss O' Coin is a road race just short of 6 miles with a small section of trail on the hills above, Birdsedge, Shepley and Jackson Bridge. Starting and Finishing at the Toss O' Coin pub on a glorious summers day it should be great fun for all the family. Plus there is a secret twist just waiting for you.
fields.description: Toss O' Coin is a road race just short of 6 miles with a small section of trail on the hills above, Birdsedge, Shepley and Jackson Bridge. Starting and Finishing at the Toss O' Coin pub on a glorious summers day it should be great fun for all the family. Plus there is a special twist just waiting for you. Will the route be clockwise or anticlockwise?

fields.name: Shepley 10k
fields.keyinfo: 10k on the picturesque country lanes around Shepley.
fields.description:
Shepley Cricket Club host the Shepley 10k a hilly road race with a kid's fun run and family day afterwards. The route is a anti-clockwise route with a fast start and fast finish but a killer middle section. Can you conquer the picturesque hills.

A Road Race over a certified accurate 10km course.

fields.name: The Stairway to Heaven
fields.keyinfo: 13km of mixed road and trail around the Holmbridge and Holme Styes.
fields.description:
Stairway To Heaven is a challenging, hilly course towards Ramsden reservoir and the forested paths around Hade Edge. Climb from the reservoirs of Holmbridge to Elysium farm and down to Holme Styes before climbing back up and home. Approx 13km (8.5 miles). The event HQ is Holmbridge Church Hall.

Summer Wine Trails events include the main trail race as well as a Challenge Walk version which sets off 1 hour earlier as well as children's races. All our events are be licenced and insured through the Association of Running Clubs.

fields.name: The Peak District Challenge
fields.keyinfo: Choose from any of our selected routes and enjoy a beautiful run in the Peak District.
fields.description: Download one of our recommended routes, hand picked by experienced trail runners, and enjoy running through some of the UK's most iconic trail running scenery. Earn one of our amazing medals for your collection.

fields.name: The Lake District Challenge
fields.keyinfo: Choose from any of our selected routes and enjoy a beautiful run in the Lake District or invent your own.
fields.description: Download one of our recommended routes, hand picked by experienced trail runners, and enjoy running through some of the UK's most iconic trail running scenery. Earn one of our amazing medals for your collection.

fields.name: The Brecon Beacons Challenge
fields.keyinfo: Choose from any of our selected routes and enjoy a beautiful run in the Brecon Beacons.
fields.description: Download one of our recommended routes, hand picked by experienced trail runners, and enjoy running through some of the UK's most iconic trail running scenery. Earn one of our amazing medals for your collection.

fields.name: London Landmarks
fields.keyinfo: Race your own virtual 10k. Snap a selfie with Big Ben. Earn your medal.
fields.description: This is part of the UK Landmarks virtual medal collection. Run your own 10k through our capital and snap a selfie with Big Ben. Send in your photo and earn your amazing medal.

fields.description: Compete with other runners from across the UK. This long established festival of running will get your blood pumping. Enter the rest of our city based races.
